### Using the law of sines

According to the law of sines:

$\dfrac{AB}{\sin(C)}=\dfrac{BC}{\sin(A)}$

We are given that $\blueE{\text m\angle A=28\degree}$, $\maroonE{\text m\angle C=83\degree}$, and $\goldE{BC=50\,\text{m}}$. Let's plug in these values and solve.

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{AB}{\sin(\maroonE{83\degree})}&=\dfrac{\goldE{50\,\text{m}}}{\sin(\blueE{28\degree})}
\\\\
AB &= \dfrac{50\,\text{m} \cdot \sin(83\degree) }{\sin(28\degree) } \\\\
AB &\approx 106 \,\text{m}
\end{align}$
